Basic food but convenient if you stay at the hotel.

Good sized pizza I personally would've preferred more cheese but other than that the pizza was great. My Shirley temple tasted a little funky; and the waiter was hard to understand and very one track minded we had a hard time asking for more than one thing at a time. It was also only outdoor dining despite it saying inside dining.
8 years later and its still that good, we've moved to the West Side now but will always make a pilgrimage back for a few glasses at the best wine bar we know and love.
Best place in seaport village
Why are your hours posted as open on Sunday when you’re not? I walked 15 mins to this place to find out that it’s closed.

Their from scratch pizza is the best! Clean, fast, and super friendly bartenders and other staff. Affordable prices for a downtown classy restaurant. Almost seems like a sports bar with their TVs, diverse beer selection and their delicious food.

Great service and amazing food. We arrived shortly before closing but they were very hospitable and didn't make us feel like we were imposing. We thought it closed later according to Google as we don't like to be the people who come in at …
A favorite place for quality pizza. i love this place always quality food & service. really nothing but good experiences here. the bill was well within reason for the quality.

FYI this place closes at 9:40 and all I wanted was some drinks to go and they were closed. Covid hours aren’t clear on website, Yelp, Google or signage posted outside. I was staying at the hotel and they couldn’t even help. You’re better off spending your money elsewhere
10/10 beat place i have been to
Tasty food, good staff. Just expensive for what you get.
Fantastic and flavorful food, I like the ambience this spot has, and the staff members were very kind. I will definitely eat here again.

What a great little hidden gem located on embassy suites property. Very easy to pass by. Nice weekday specials but the regular menu is traffic as well. A number of exceptional and eclectic menu items as well as some very fine craft beers! …
Bartender was awesome
good
Excellent service and the food was awesome
Pizza is good but it’s California pizza.  I would have given better review but I was virtually ignored while bartender made nice with other patrons.  Guess tips don’t matter to him.  2/17/2020.  4ish
They gave me a raw cheesesteak. I took it back and they nuked it in the microwave. Minimum wage at its finest
Decent for a hotel restaurant that doesn't carry a big name.
Walked 20 minutes to get to there and and they were closed 45 minutes before their advertised time.
Best thin crust pizza in San Diego
We had the best Margarita pizza! First time and hopefully not the last! When we come back to our Grandsons wedding!

Chose it on Xmas night, waited 20min. Staff are super friendly, pizza is very delicious, we also ordered sides like grilled asparagus, roasted sprouts and pasta with source, all delicious and big portion. We enjoyed this dinner!
Great pizza and service for the price, but the place was a little empty.
Excellent food, good service, quality establishment
Good thin Pizza. Perfect for a later quick dinner. One of the only late night places in the area. Much better then Kansas City BBQ.

Good pizza at a decent price. We tried the classic pepperoni and another one called the caracota, so good. Service was friendly and fast. No complaints today. They had sports on. It was a slow thanksgiving day lunch.
Very fresh ingredients. Good sports bar vibe. Connected to Embassy Suites so real handy for guests
Wood fired pizza is awesome. We had pepperoni and sausage and it was great.
Quiet. Liked the atmosphere and food.
Wait was slow and pizza wasn't great.

In embassy suites, friendly and decent food and calamari. Decent is good for calamari as bad is the norm. Had it the night before better but 3x the price. So good affordable food and you get better quality than expected here

Great place to eat. Located at the bottom of embassy suites downtown (access from inside or outside). Ive had their garlic wings and a pizza. Unfortunately I didn't take any pictures but I will when I come again. Looking forward to try something new here!
Delicious food and excellent service.
Good west coast pizza. Cant live up to NYC slices but a great variety in a small bar atmosphere.

Ate here off of some vouchers from the hotel. It was convenient, quick and surprisingly delicious! I had the seafood fettuccine and there was a lot of seafood and the pasta and sauce was tasty. I was skeptical, but it was solid food and …

Service was good and water was polite, but at 7pm on a Tuesday it was pretty dead. Ordered the calamari and it was fried to the point it was hardly edible, like eating rubber bands... Pizza was good, but not great.
Good food. Good service.

We went on a Sunday evening, for dinner. They seemed short staffed, and it was busy. They tried their best, but we had to wait for service and then food. Food was excellent and I would go again. Two of us got a pizza, and we liked them. Hopefully next time they aren't so busy.

The service was terrible, from the confusion of do we seat ourselves or wait to be seated to trying to get the bill. The food, when finally ordered, took so long to arrive. The margarita pizza was so garlicky it was inedible. Drinks were not refilled, silverware for salads had to be requested.
Great food, great drinks and reasonable prices especially for downtown...

I ate lunch here while attending a conference.  It was pretty early so the bartender was asking serving my meal.  The food was good, but as with most places near the convention center the prices for the food were a little high.

The pizza was good and the beer selection is decent. Only thing I wouldn't recommend are the stuffed onion rings. They came out soggy, tasted like grease, and had zero cheesesteak flavor. Fortunately the bar tender took them off the bill without question.
Was told "it was going to be easier on them if we went elsewhere"......We went elsewhere.........great customer service!  WOW!
What you'd expect from a hotel restaurant

Good food, SLOW service. I went to lunch at NY West with 2 of my colleagues. It took about 10 minutes for anyone to acknowledge us - that was the first red flag. We ordered our food (appetizers and entrees), and about 20 minutes later the …
Great food. Love it!
Waiter was great. Ben (I think). He said he has Scottish ancestors. Pizza was great. Salad also.
Great pizza! Ordered without parmesan and was no problem. Great service too!

This was our last lunch in San Diego and we were very pleased with it!! We started with the Lobster Deviled Eggs and WOW they were soooooo good! Then we had the Curgine Pizza and it was great as well! Our waiter was fast and attentive and the atmosphere was pleasent! Bravo New York West!!

GrubHub failed to deliver but NY West quickly remade my order for pick-up. Great service and friendly staff. Pizza's had generous and fresh toppings. I've never had a Margharita with garlic before but it was very good. Pizza's tasted great. If you are expecting NY style pizza though, it's not.
Nasty, Margherita pizza was super greasy. Food was way over priced.

I had a great cheese steak sandwich that tasted delicious. French fries were tasty. There were more than a dozen beers on tap with local selection for us visitors.  The beers and side salad were very pricey. I was caught off guard, but it's …
Very good pizza, wings, calamari, asparagus, brussel sprouts. Many beer choices. Service just okay.

We arrived 40 minutes ago. Only three other tables.  Still no food but that's not the bad part.  My husband ordered any elysian draft. There was lipstick on the glass.  He pointed it out and the server just poured it into another glass.  If that's their way of solving that issue, it deeply concerns me.  How's their kitchen cleanliness?

I tripped on this restaurant while searching for NY Pizza near me.  Ive seen it before when walking by (spend a lot of rime across the street at the Hyatt and shop at Office Depot) but never contemplated going in until I rwad the reviews. …

Went here while in town from TX. Heard about the food and it was amazing. Wings to die for and Pizza was insane. Had the Corleone (Cheesesteak) pizza and was to die for and craved for more when it was gone. Ordered the Pepperoni as well and …

The best chicken wings I ever had. They're thick like drumsticks and good quality chicken. The homemade pizza bites and dipping sauces are really good and the pizzas are gourmet quality. Great atmosphere, classy but casual, friendly staff, full bar and awesome selection of beers, and reasonable prices. I'll definitely be back.
Decent food and nice downtown environment. Parked at seaport village and walked. Recommend happy hour specials. Delicious pizza.

Only went in because my 6 year old wanted pizza. Nice surprise! good bar (std old fashioned made with Irish whiskey). Get the cheese steak stuffed onion rings!! and the cioppino if available. In the Embassy Suites

I got the fish taco app. I usually love fish and really enjoy fish tacos. Theses were gross. The worst fish taste. Blah...  I’ve lived in Japan, I’ve eaten a lot of fish. Don’t get this. The stuffed onion was delicious; probably shortened my life by a few years. Decent beer selection. Waitress was nice.
Shared an appetizer with a friend, ask for Will
In the Embassy Suites. Very good food. Very nice staff

We had dinner here on 9-16-2018 between 5:00 and 6:30. This is a great restaurant. There are several TVs to watch the football game. Dinner and appetizers were fantastic and came out in a timely manner. The wait staff were very attentive and the bartender made excellent cocktails. I will definitely be here again!
Good food, attentive staff
Pizza was very good, service good.  Would have given five stars if they used Buffalo mozzarella.
Good service at the bar. Decent thin crust pizza. Fair tap list but only a few are independent craft beers. Prices are higher than average because of the hotel.

The food and atmosphere here are great. After a long day of conferencing it was good to come in to a large selection of beers. The bartender, Geza, was a joy to talk with as well. I'd recommend this to anyone. Cheers!
The lobster ravioli was delicious. The bartender (Gaza?) was great! Cool guy and makes very good drinks.
Great pizza!
Great service and great food
Great food but took a while to get. Don’t know if that was because of how big our party was but the food made up for it!
Great food and lots of cold beer on tap!  Service was first rate.
Good food and service. A little pricey, but so is everything else in downtown
We had such a great time here on the patio with the flame jet towers. Service was awesome. Pizza, salad and drinks were perfect for our group of 40!
Nice place for a few beers after work
Great place for lunch.  Good food and drink and great service!
Cool atmosphere. I ordered the chopped salad  with ranch and it was delicious. Big portions! Good service!

This restaurant is the worst in San Diego. A week ago my wife and I  placed an order for my daughter’s birthday party.We order a few kind of pizza and other dishes. I can't even explain you guys what we got!! So we send it back and called …
Friendly waiter brought us great freshly prepared food.  Fries were fantastic!  Located in same building as Embassy Suites Hotel.  Has outdoor  dining option.  Reasonable prices. Very pleased.
Nice bar and food
Great atmosphere and service.  Food is great and our server was on his toes. Joey was pur server and he deserves 5 stars.
Bartender by the name of Gayza. Cool honest man. Keeps them coming too.
MAMA MIA!! The Pizza here is MAGNIFICO!!! MUAH
Had lunch and dinner here while at Embassy Suites.  Nice service, good prices and food and drinks are good.  Had burger and pizza - great!
Great brushcetta and great service. We were helped by AJ and he was so attentive. We will definitely be coming back!
Staff is so super friendly and food was really good with generous portions!
Burger was really good. They host yappy hour  so that's a good thing and I like the lack of bun
Good food

I really enjoyed my dinner at New York West. The food was delicious (try the Consigliere pizza), the atmosphere was great, and best of all the service was amazing (Geza, I hope your manager reads these reviews)!
Ok food.  Mediocre service
Good pizza!

Great pizza, friendly service, beer selection better than most. We ordered 1/2 and 1/2 (two flavors) on one large pizza. At the time did not realize we had asked for white sauce and red sauce flavors on one pie. Most resturants don't handle …

Finally was able to try this gem of a restaurant! I tried the NYW steak burger and was very satisfied! If you haven't tried this, you need to! It was an experience like no other with the delicious stuffed onion ring on the burger. I also …

Good service, good atmosphere, was kinda quiet the night we went. I ordered a beer and a cheesesteak but humorously I got a cheesecake slice. We were both good spirits about it and they quickly replaced it with the cheese steak I actually …
Bartender was very nice and made great drinks!! The cheesesteak was authentic Philly, from the meat to the amaroso roll.  I was impressed how good it was.
Place has a good vibe, very attentive server, great food and drinks .

I love this place for hand tossed pizzas and happy hour. The beer selection is great and a full bar. The menu is large with plenty of good choices. We enjoy the patio for people watching and hanging out before our evening downtown.
Good food and beer
The food was very good and served hot. Staff courteous and attentive. All our questions were answered. Drinks from the bar were perfect
